{"type":"message","id":"1c450e8c","parentId":"114fe455","timestamp":"2026-02-17T13:28:58.263Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Considering the Command Prompt**\n\nI'm now interpreting the prompt as providing the command, given the failed search. I'm focusing on the \"guarde a liberação da cota de imagem\" part, assuming it means I'm supposed to wait for image quota release.\n\n\n**Deciphering the Instructions**\n\nI've re-examined the prompt. It's becoming clear that the system wants me to wait for image quota release before generating an image, but it's not a tool I recognize. I'm now leaning towards the idea that `openclaw image generate` might be a custom command accessible via `exec`. I'll try checking `openclaw --help` and also `openclaw image --help`.\n\n\n**Evaluating the Possibilities**\n\nOkay, so the initial assumption of using the command prompt to interpret the command to run was correct. However, after the help commands gave me no indication of any image generation, I am now focused on the instruction to \"wait... and generate\". The prompt is structured for a generation tool call, but the available `image` tool's description doesn't fit. Now, I will retry `openclaw image --help`, to see if the command can call for an image to be generated from the system.\n\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"exec_1771334938251_437","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"openclaw image --help"},"thoughtSignature":""}],"api":"google-gemini-cli","provider":"google-gemini-cli","model":"gemini-3-pro-preview","usage":{"input":1649,"output":442,"cacheRead":4132,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":6223,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1771334930469}}
{"type":"message","id":"82732dde","parentId":"1c450e8c","timestamp":"2026-02-17T13:29:07.776Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"exec_1771334938251_437","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"🦞 OpenClaw 2026.2.14 (c1feda1) — Turning \"I'll reply later\" into \"my bot replied instantly\".\n\nUsage: openclaw [options] [command]\n\nOptions:\n  --dev             Dev profile: isolate state under ~/.openclaw-dev, default\n                    gateway port 19001, and shift derived ports (browser/canvas)\n  -h, --help        display help for command\n  --no-color        Disable ANSI colors\n  --profile <name>  Use a named profile (isolates\n                    OPENCLAW_STATE_DIR/OPENCLAW_CONFIG_PATH under\n                    ~/.openclaw-<name>)\n  -V, --version     output the version number\n\nCommands:\n  acp               Agent Control Protocol tools\n  agent             Agent commands\n  agents            Manage isolated agents\n  approvals         Exec approvals\n  browser           Browser tools\n  channels          Channel management\n  completion        Generate shell completion script\n  config            Config helpers\n  configure         Configure wizard\n  cron              Cron scheduler\n  daemon            Gateway service (legacy alias)\n  dashboard         Open the Control UI with your current token\n  devices           Device pairing + token management\n  directory         Directory commands\n  dns               DNS helpers\n  docs              Docs helpers\n  doctor            Health checks + quick fixes for the gateway and channels\n  gateway           Gateway control\n  health            Gateway health\n  help              display help for command\n  hooks             Hooks tooling\n  logs              Gateway logs\n  memory            Memory commands\n  message           Send, read, and manage messages\n  models            Model configuration\n  node              Node control\n  nodes             Node commands\n  onboard           Onboarding helpers\n  pairing           Pairing helpers\n  plugins           Plugin management\n  reset             Reset local config/state (keeps the CLI installed)\n  sandbox           Sandbox tools\n  security          Security helpers\n  sessions          Session management\n  setup             Setup helpers\n  skills            Skills management\n  status            Gateway status\n  system            System events, heartbeat, and presence\n  tui               Terminal UI\n  uninstall         Uninstall the gateway service + local data (CLI remains)\n  update            CLI update helpers\n  webhooks          Webhook helpers\n\nExamples:\n  openclaw channels login --verbose\n    Link personal WhatsApp Web and show QR + connection logs.\n  openclaw message send --target +15555550123 --message \"Hi\" --json\n    Send via your web session and print JSON result.\n  openclaw gateway --port 18789\n    Run the WebSocket Gateway locally.\n  openclaw --dev gateway\n    Run a dev Gateway (isolated state/config) on ws://127.0.0.1:19001.\n  openclaw gateway --force\n    Kill anything bound to the default gateway port, then start it.\n  openclaw gateway ...\n    Gateway control via WebSocket.\n  openclaw agent --to +15555550123 --message \"Run summary\" --deliver\n    Talk directly to the agent using the Gateway; optionally send the WhatsApp reply.\n  openclaw message send --channel telegram --target @mychat --message \"Hi\"\n    Send via your Telegram bot.\n\nDocs: https://docs.openclaw.ai/cli"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":9500,"aggregated":"🦞 OpenClaw 2026.2.14 (c1feda1) — Turning \"I'll reply later\" into \"my bot replied instantly\".\n\nUsage: openclaw [options] [command]\n\nOptions:\n  --dev             Dev profile: isolate state under ~/.openclaw-dev, default\n                    gateway port 19001, and shift derived ports (browser/canvas)\n  -h, --help        display help for command\n  --no-color        Disable ANSI colors\n  --profile <name>  Use a named profile (isolates\n                    OPENCLAW_STATE_DIR/OPENCLAW_CONFIG_PATH under\n                    ~/.openclaw-<name>)\n  -V, --version     output the version number\n\nCommands:\n  acp               Agent Control Protocol tools\n  agent             Agent commands\n  agents            Manage isolated agents\n  approvals         Exec approvals\n  browser           Browser tools\n  channels          Channel management\n  completion        Generate shell completion script\n  config            Config helpers\n  configure         Configure wizard\n  cron              Cron scheduler\n  daemon            Gateway service (legacy alias)\n  dashboard         Open the Control UI with your current token\n  devices           Device pairing + token management\n  directory         Directory commands\n  dns               DNS helpers\n  docs              Docs helpers\n  doctor            Health checks + quick fixes for the gateway and channels\n  gateway           Gateway control\n  health            Gateway health\n  help              display help for command\n  hooks             Hooks tooling\n  logs              Gateway logs\n  memory            Memory commands\n  message           Send, read, and manage messages\n  models            Model configuration\n  node              Node control\n  nodes             Node commands\n  onboard           Onboarding helpers\n  pairing           Pairing helpers\n  plugins           Plugin management\n  reset             Reset local config/state (keeps the CLI installed)\n  sandbox           Sandbox tools\n  security          Security helpers\n  sessions          Session management\n  setup             Setup helpers\n  skills            Skills management\n  status            Gateway status\n  system            System events, heartbeat, and presence\n  tui               Terminal UI\n  uninstall         Uninstall the gateway service + local data (CLI remains)\n  update            CLI update helpers\n  webhooks          Webhook helpers\n\nExamples:\n  openclaw channels login --verbose\n    Link personal WhatsApp Web and show QR + connection logs.\n  openclaw message send --target +15555550123 --message \"Hi\" --json\n    Send via your web session and print JSON result.\n  openclaw gateway --port 18789\n    Run the WebSocket Gateway locally.\n  openclaw --dev gateway\n    Run a dev Gateway (isolated state/config) on ws://127.0.0.1:19001.\n  openclaw gateway --force\n    Kill anything bound to the default gateway port, then start it.\n  openclaw gateway ...\n    Gateway control via WebSocket.\n  openclaw agent --to +15555550123 --message \"Run summary\" --deliver\n    Talk directly to the agent using the Gateway; optionally send the WhatsApp reply.\n  openclaw message send --channel telegram --target @mychat --message \"Hi\"\n    Send via your Telegram bot.\n\nDocs: https://docs.openclaw.ai/cli","cwd":"/home/franklinbaldo/.openclaw/agents/aparicio/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1771334947764}}
