{"type":"message","id":"6a03c7c6","parentId":"f2d2b520","timestamp":"2026-02-17T13:29:37.482Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Examining Script Options**\n\nI've located two relevant scripts: `generate_image_flash.py` and `generate_imagen_fast.py`. The request for a \"DEFINITIVE version\" coupled with \"Imagen Fast\" for speed and \"Image Flash\" hinting at swiftness, suggests focusing on the user's desire for rapid generation. The \"Aguarde a liberação da cota\" implies a quota to manage.\n\n\n**Evaluating Script Content**\n\nI've decided to examine `generate_image_flash.py` closely. The goal is to see if it accepts a prompt and an output path. If it does, then it's a prime candidate for the definitive version. The prompt's focus on quality suggests that `generate_image_flash.py` might be preferred, if it offers better model options, even if at the expense of speed.\n\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"read_1771334977465_440","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"scripts/generate_image_flash.py","limit":100},"thoughtSignature":""}],"api":"google-gemini-cli","provider":"google-gemini-cli","model":"gemini-3-pro-preview","usage":{"input":926,"output":234,"cacheRead":6547,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":7707,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1771334967192}}
{"type":"message","id":"b1d96728","parentId":"6a03c7c6","timestamp":"2026-02-17T13:29:37.531Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"read_1771334977465_440","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"#!/usr/bin/env python3\n# /// script\n# requires-python = \">=3.10\"\n# dependencies = [\n#     \"google-genai>=1.0.0\",\n#     \"pillow>=10.0.0\",\n# ]\n# ///\nimport argparse\nimport os\nimport sys\nfrom pathlib import Path\n\ndef get_api_key(provided_key: str | None) -> str | None:\n    if provided_key:\n        return provided_key\n    return os.environ.get(\"GEMINI_API_KEY\")\n\ndef main():\n    parser = argparse.ArgumentParser()\n    parser.add_argument(\"--prompt\", \"-p\", required=True)\n    parser.add_argument(\"--filename\", \"-f\", required=True)\n    parser.add_argument(\"--resolution\", \"-r\", choices=[\"1K\", \"2K\", \"4K\"], default=\"1K\")\n    parser.add_argument(\"--api-key\", \"-k\")\n    parser.add_argument(\"--model\", \"-m\", default=\"gemini-2.5-flash-image\")\n    args = parser.parse_args()\n\n    api_key = get_api_key(args.api_key)\n    if not api_key:\n        sys.exit(1)\n\n    from google import genai\n    from google.genai import types\n    from PIL import Image as PILImage\n\n    client = genai.Client(api_key=api_key)\n    output_path = Path(args.filename)\n    output_path.parent.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)\n\n    print(f\"Generating image with model {args.model} and resolution {args.resolution}...\")\n\n    try:\n        response = client.models.generate_content(\n            model=args.model,\n            contents=args.prompt,\n            config=types.GenerateContentConfig(\n                response_modalities=[\"TEXT\", \"IMAGE\"],\n                image_config=types.ImageConfig(\n                    image_size=args.resolution\n                )\n            )\n        )\n\n        image_saved = False\n        for part in response.parts:\n            if part.inline_data is not None:\n                from io import BytesIO\n                image_data = part.inline_data.data\n                if isinstance(image_data, str):\n                    import base64\n                    image_data = base64.b64decode(image_data)\n\n                image = PILImage.open(BytesIO(image_data))\n                if image.mode == 'RGBA':\n                    rgb_image = PILImage.new('RGB', image.size, (255, 255, 255))\n                    rgb_image.paste(image, mask=image.split()[3])\n                    rgb_image.save(str(output_path), 'PNG')\n                else:\n                    image.convert('RGB').save(str(output_path), 'PNG')\n                image_saved = True\n\n        if image_saved:\n            print(f\"\\nImage saved: {output_path.resolve()}\")\n            print(f\"MEDIA: {output_path.resolve()}\")\n        else:\n            print(\"Error: No image generated.\")\n            sys.exit(1)\n\n    except Exception as e:\n        print(f\"Error: {e}\")\n        sys.exit(1)\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    main()\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1771334977520}}
{"type":"message","id":"c8a8a323","parentId":"b1d96728","timestamp":"2026-02-17T13:29:42.627Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Reviewing File Interactions**\n\nI'm now revisiting the file interactions. I initially thought I had read the file, but realized I only *requested* to read it. Now, I see the request was fulfilled. The file uses `google-genai`. I need to ensure that is installed.\n\n\n**Confirming File Contents**\n\nI'm correcting my course. I need to read the file `scripts/generate_image_flash.py` to confirm its arguments. The previous step only requested the read action. It is essential I obtain the actual content to proceed.\n\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"read_1771334982609_441","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"scripts/generate_image_flash.py"},"thoughtSignature":""}],"api":"google-gemini-cli","provider":"google-gemini-cli","model":"gemini-3-pro-preview","usage":{"input":1560,"output":217,"cacheRead":6892,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":8669,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1771334977531}}
{"type":"message","id":"19438c38","parentId":"c8a8a323","timestamp":"2026-02-17T13:29:42.665Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"read_1771334982609_441","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"#!/usr/bin/env python3\n# /// script\n# requires-python = \">=3.10\"\n# dependencies = [\n#     \"google-genai>=1.0.0\",\n#     \"pillow>=10.0.0\",\n# ]\n# ///\nimport argparse\nimport os\nimport sys\nfrom pathlib import Path\n\ndef get_api_key(provided_key: str | None) -> str | None:\n    if provided_key:\n        return provided_key\n    return os.environ.get(\"GEMINI_API_KEY\")\n\ndef main():\n    parser = argparse.ArgumentParser()\n    parser.add_argument(\"--prompt\", \"-p\", required=True)\n    parser.add_argument(\"--filename\", \"-f\", required=True)\n    parser.add_argument(\"--resolution\", \"-r\", choices=[\"1K\", \"2K\", \"4K\"], default=\"1K\")\n    parser.add_argument(\"--api-key\", \"-k\")\n    parser.add_argument(\"--model\", \"-m\", default=\"gemini-2.5-flash-image\")\n    args = parser.parse_args()\n\n    api_key = get_api_key(args.api_key)\n    if not api_key:\n        sys.exit(1)\n\n    from google import genai\n    from google.genai import types\n    from PIL import Image as PILImage\n\n    client = genai.Client(api_key=api_key)\n    output_path = Path(args.filename)\n    output_path.parent.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)\n\n    print(f\"Generating image with model {args.model} and resolution {args.resolution}...\")\n\n    try:\n        response = client.models.generate_content(\n            model=args.model,\n            contents=args.prompt,\n            config=types.GenerateContentConfig(\n                response_modalities=[\"TEXT\", \"IMAGE\"],\n                image_config=types.ImageConfig(\n                    image_size=args.resolution\n                )\n            )\n        )\n\n        image_saved = False\n        for part in response.parts:\n            if part.inline_data is not None:\n                from io import BytesIO\n                image_data = part.inline_data.data\n                if isinstance(image_data, str):\n                    import base64\n                    image_data = base64.b64decode(image_data)\n\n                image = PILImage.open(BytesIO(image_data))\n                if image.mode == 'RGBA':\n                    rgb_image = PILImage.new('RGB', image.size, (255, 255, 255))\n                    rgb_image.paste(image, mask=image.split()[3])\n                    rgb_image.save(str(output_path), 'PNG')\n                else:\n                    image.convert('RGB').save(str(output_path), 'PNG')\n                image_saved = True\n\n        if image_saved:\n            print(f\"\\nImage saved: {output_path.resolve()}\")\n            print(f\"MEDIA: {output_path.resolve()}\")\n        else:\n            print(\"Error: No image generated.\")\n            sys.exit(1)\n\n    except Exception as e:\n        print(f\"Error: {e}\")\n        sys.exit(1)\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    main()\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1771334982657}}
{"type":"message","id":"f8ce79d0","parentId":"19438c38","timestamp":"2026-02-17T13:29:58.948Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Investigating Image Generation Scripts**\n\nI've been looking at the `scripts/generate_image_flash.py` script and its options. It seems straightforward, taking a prompt, filename, resolution, and model. It relies on the `google-genai` library and an API key. I also noticed another script, `generate_imagen_fast.py`, which is intriguing. I'm now comparing the two.\n\n\n**Refining Execution Strategy**\n\nI'm now formulating the precise command. It will involve a sleep command, followed by the image generation script call. The prompt is finalized, including details about the image style, subject, and scene. I'll include error checking, waiting for the quota, then sending the finished image to Adi.\n\n\n**Orchestrating the Execution**\n\nI've crafted a single command, incorporating a sleep, image generation via `generate_image_flash.py` with a detailed prompt and filename, and error checking to see if the file exists. The next step is to execute this as a background process with `exec` and a 1200s timeout. To ensure robust handling, I'll poll for the file's presence after the `exec` call. If successful, I'll then use the `message` tool separately.\n\n\n**Planning the Execution Loop**\n\nI'm now detailing the command for the image generation. It will include a `sleep` of 360 seconds before running `generate_image_flash.py` with the prompt and filename. After the generation, I'll use `if [ -s ... ]` to check the file's size. The command's output will determine file availability, crucial for subsequent actions. I plan to use `exec` with a background process and then utilize the `process` tool to poll for completion, ensuring proper timing and file presence before sending a message.\n\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"exec_1771334998931_443","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"sleep 400 && python3 scripts/generate_image_flash.py --prompt \"Estilo: Xilogravura ou gravura antiga em papel envelhecido, preto e branco. Um velho gaúcho alto e imponente (Vovô Franquelim), vestindo um pala gaúcho tradicional sobre os ombros (cinza com orla preta), chapéu de aba larga e lenço no pescoço. Ele está no pátio de uma estância, apontando para o céu com semblante sério e autoritário. No céu, dois pequenos aviões teco-tecos da década de 1950 voam baixo sobre as copas das árvores. Ao lado dele, outro gaúcho (Gaudêncio), um velho com bigodes brancos fartos e compridos, olha para o céu com expressão de total espanto e boca aberta. Ao fundo, um galpão de madeira rústico e árvores típicas do pampa rio-grandense.\" --filename \"assets/images/20260217154000_da7fbb4a_causo-teco-teco-gravura-final.png\"","background":true},"thoughtSignature":""}],"api":"google-gemini-cli","provider":"google-gemini-cli","model":"gemini-3-pro-preview","usage":{"input":2214,"output":1218,"cacheRead":7151,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":10583,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1771334982666}}
